The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 18 August is 2,862 (331.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 14 August, there were 32 new confirmed cases (3.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 07 August, there were 21 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 52% (11 extra cases).
